The paper discusses query languages and their computational properties, which is a topic closely related to databases and logic. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions finite model theory and benchmark workloads, which are topics that fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of query evaluation, which is a topic that falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
